ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would strongly recommend Economics 737 -- especially for students who are looking for a class that allows them to apply economic theory to important, real-world scenarios. I would also recommend Economics 737 to anyone with an interest in the environment or environmental management.
Absolutely. I learned a lot, and a lot of it I will remember.
The course is very well-taught and a pleasure to attend.
I would recommend it for someone specifically interested in environmental subjects; however, I do not think it is relevant for other students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have a strong interest in environmental issues. As a student of economics, this course allowed me to understand and utilise the tools required for the management of global natural resources.
I had never been taught a similar subject before so every class that I attended I learn something new.
It did not. It was simply to fulfill a requirement.
gave me a great understanding of how economics can fit into my career direction, and I am considering continuing in this direction of economics and natural resources
